The company’s expansion can be traced through a series of strategic acquisitions, each more ambitious than the last, culminating in the 1970s with the purchase of several **[Independent_bookstore](/Independent_bookstore)** chains across Southeast Asia. This period cemented MPH’s reputation as the **[Corporate_governance](/Corporate_governance)** equivalent of a Swiss‑army knife: versatile, slightly rusty, but somehow still useful.  

